'''Lenya National Park''' is a national park located in the [[Tenasserim Hills]], [[Burma]] in the border area with [[Thailand]],<ref name="short">[http://protectedplanet.net/sites/Lenya_National_Park Protected Planet UNEP-WCMC]</ref> limiting with the [[Namtok Huai Yang National Park]]. The park consists of 176,638 hectares of [[tropical evergreen forest|lowland tropical forest]].<ref name="short" /><ref>[http://birdlifeindochina.org/birdlife/report_pdfs/pr_gurney%27s_pitta_news_release_28_nov_eng.pdf Lenya: Myanmar’s Hidden Treasure - Birdlife Intl.]</ref>
The main purpose of the national park is the maintenance of [[natural resource]]s. The demarcation is in course. It is governed by the Burma Forest Department and the level of protection is partial, for [[logging]] and forest plantations are allowed. The altitudes within the park range from 10 to 855 m. The endangered [[Gurney's pitta]], endemic to Thailand and Myanmar, is found within the park.<ref>[http://www.banca-env.org/ebook.pdf Myanmar Protected Areas - Context, Current Status and Challenges] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120417063155/http://www.banca-env.org/ebook.pdf |date=2012-04-17 }}</ref> ==See also== *[[List of protected areas in Burma]]
