'''Wet rot''' is a [[generic term]] used to define a [[Paraphyly|variety]] of [[Fungus|fungal]] [[species]], such as ''[[Coniophora puteana]]'' ([[Common name|otherwise known]] as [[cellar fungus]]). Wet rot fungi obtain their [[food]] by [[decomposition|breaking down]] the [[cell wall]]s of [[wood cell]]s resulting in a loss of strength of the [[wood]]. This can cause problems in the [[Structural integrity and failure|structural integrity]] of [[structure]]s.

